**Tip**: Ek hi format (RGB ya HSL) pura project mein use karo.

### 4. Useful CSS Functions

| Function       | Matlab                                      | Example |
|----------------|---------------------------------------------|---------|
| `calc()`       | Math karo (different units mix)             | `width: calc(50% + 20px);` |
| `var()`        | CSS Custom Properties (variables)           | `color: var(--primary, blue);` |
| `min()` / `max()` / `clamp()` | Minimum, maximum, ya clamp value     | `font-size: clamp(1rem, 2vw, 2rem);` |
| `rgb()` / `hsl()` | Colors with functions                    | `background: hsl(200 50% 50%);` |

### 5. Quick Tips & Gotchas

- **Percentages** hamesha relative hote hain (parent ke hisaab se). Kuch properties mein `%` allowed nahi hota (jaise `border-width`).
- `px` fixed hota hai → responsive design mein kam use karo.
- `rem` sabse safe aur scalable unit hai modern websites ke liye.
- Unitless numbers allowed hain kuch jagah (jaise `opacity: 0.7`).
- High DPI screens (mobile) par `px` physical pixel se alag ho sakta hai.
- Hamesha responsive banane ke liye **relative units** (`rem`, `%`, `vh/vw`) prefer karo.

**Basic Example**:
```css
body {
  font-size: 1.125rem;        /* rem = root se */
  line-height: 1.5;
}

.container {
  width: 90%;                 /* % of parent */
  max-width: 1200px;          /* mix with px */
  padding: 2rem;              /* rem spacing */
  background: hsl(200 80% 60%);
}